### Variaveis
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@authEmail = "admin@example.com"
@authPassword = "password123"

### 1. Health & DB
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
---
GET {{baseUrl}}/db/ping

### 2. Signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": {{authEmail}},
  "password": {{authPassword}},
  "tenantName": "Example Corp"
}

### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": {{authEmail}},
  "password": {{authPassword}}
}

### 4. Fetch User Session (Me)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
# The token is sent automatically if your HTTP client saves cookies

### 5. List Tenants
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants

### 6. Create another Tenant
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Second Tenant"
}

### 7. Select Tenant (switch context)
# Change the tenantId below to a valid one returned by GET /tenants
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants/select
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenantId": "REPLACE_WITH_VALID_UUID"
}

### Select Tenant B
POST http://localhost:3333/tenants/select
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "tenantId": "{{TENANT_B_ID}}"
}

###

// ==========================================
// STEP 2: Canonical Data Model Endpoints
// Verify Multi-Tenancy Isolation
// ==========================================

### Get Orders (Will return only orders for the currently selected tenant)
GET http://localhost:3333/orders?limit=10&offset=0
Content-Type: application/json

### Get specific order by ID (replace with order A1 ID or order B1 ID)
GET http://localhost:3333/orders/00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000000A1
Content-Type: application/json

### Get Returns (Will return only returns for the currently selected tenant)
GET http://localhost:3333/returns?limit=10&offset=0
Content-Type: application/json

### Get specific return by ID (replace with a valid ID from the list above)
GET http://localhost:3333/returns/REPLACE_WITH_RETURN_ID
Content-Type: application/json

###

// To prove isolation:
// 1. Login with ownerA@seed.com
// 2. Call GET /orders. You should see "ext-order-A1".
// 3. Login with ownerB@seed.com
// 4. Call GET /orders. You should see "ext-order-B1".
// 5. While logged as B, try accessing specific order A1 ID. It should return 404.
### 8. Scope Check (must happen after successful login/select)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenant/scope-check


// ==========================================
// STEP 5: Risk Engine MVP (Score 0-100)
// Verify Explainability via endpoints (Render)
// ==========================================

### 1) Get Returns with Score & Tags
GET {{baseUrl}}/returns
# Will now include `latest_score` and `latest_reasons_tags`

### 2) Get Return Details with Full AI Explainability
GET {{baseUrl}}/returns/REPLACE_WITH_RETURN_ID/details

### 3) Trigger Score Re-computation (Background Job)
# Note: Ensure you uploaded features for this ID first.
POST {{baseUrl}}/returns/REPLACE_WITH_RETURN_ID/compute-score

###
# -------------------------------------------------------------
# ETAPA 6: WORKFLOW ANTIFRAUDE (Coda de Casos e Decisoes)
# -------------------------------------------------------------

### 1) List Open Cases (Returns awaiting decision)
# Sorted automatically by highest Score then largest value
GET {{baseUrl}}/cases
Cookie: token={{USER_TOKEN}}

### 2) Decide a Case
# Resolves a case and drops it from the Queue. Requires role: admin/owner
# Allowed decisions: "approve", "reject", "request_evidence"
POST {{baseUrl}}/cases/REPLACE_WITH_RETURN_ID/decision
Cookie: token={{USER_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "decision": "reject",
    "note": "Fraud confirmed by high AI score on fast return policy abuse"
}

###
# Passo 7 - Relatórios e ROI (Metrics)

# GET /metrics/summary
# Range: 7d, 30d, 90d
GET {{API_BASE_URL}}/metrics/summary?range=30d
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###
# GET /metrics/top-reasons
GET {{API_BASE_URL}}/metrics/top-reasons?range=30d&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###
# GET /metrics/top-customers
GET {{API_BASE_URL}}/metrics/top-customers?range=90d&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

###
# -------------------------------------------------------------
# ETAPA 8: Conector Shopify
# -------------------------------------------------------------

### Install Shopify (Start OAuth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/connectors/shopify/install
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: token={{USER_TOKEN}}

{
  "shopDomain": "minha-loja-teste.myshopify.com"
}

### List Connectors
GET {{baseUrl}}/connectors
Cookie: token={{USER_TOKEN}}

### Trigger Manual Sync
POST {{baseUrl}}/connectors/{{CONNECTOR_ID}}/sync
Cookie: token={{USER_TOKEN}}
